WorldStage NewsOnline—-President Muhammadu Buhari has promised to continue to engage all parties as his administration would be operating an open government for the general progress of the country. Buhari stated this on Wednesday in Abuja while receiving his Certificate of Return from the Chairman of the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC), Prof Mahmood Yakubu. The President vowed to continue the fight against corruption, saying accumulation of public wealth would not be tolerated. He assured Nigerians that they would soon see “a country moving to the `Next Level’ as the APC-led administration consolidates on its achievements”. INEC on Wednesday morning announced Buhari as the winner of the last Saturday’s presidential election under the platform of the All Progressives Congress (APC).